Two Journalists Detained in Yemen, U.K. Embassy Says

-- B y   M o h a m m e d   H a t e m
-- 
2011-03-14T18:38:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-14/two-journalists-detained-in-yemen-u-k-embassy-says-1-.html
Two British journalists were
detained in the Yemeni capital today, Daisy Organ, media officer
for the U.K. Embassy in Sanaâ€™a, said in a telephone interview.
The embassy is in contact with the Yemeni government over the
detentions, she said.  Authorities also deported two other American journalists,
the al-Masdar independent news website said.  The two U.K. journalists are Portia Walker, who writes for
the Washington Post, and Oliver Holmes, who writes for the Wall
Street Journal and Time magazine. The two Americans are Haley
Edwards, who writes for the Los Angeles Times, and the Atlantic
Magazine, and Joshua Maricich, a photographer.  Editors: Louis Meixler, Bill Koenig  To contact the reporter on this story:
